        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Goliad </placeName><date when="1835-09-16">September 16th 1835</date></p>

<p><persName>Col. S. F. Austin</persName></p>
<p>My Dear Sir</p>
<p>I congratulate you upon your safe return to <placeName>Texas </placeName>and hope your
presence will inspire sentiments of harmony, unanimity of opinion and
firmness of purpose and extend over our <placeName>adopted country</placeName> the mantle of
peace and tranquility&#8212;</p>

<p>Your old friend <persName>D. Juan Jose Herndz. [Hernandez]</persName> is no more he fell
a victim to cholera his <persName>widow </persName>is well&#8212; The <persName>Vasquez's</persName> are also well
and these and all your <persName>friends <placeName>in this Section</placeName></persName> rejoice at your return and
desire your weal&#8212; I flatter myself with the hope that I shall enjoy the
pleasure of receiving a line from you&#8212; You can command my services
and be assured that I am Your friend and well wisher</p>

<p><persName>Thomas G. Western</persName></p>

        </div1>
